Second Foundation</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 327<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/18/02 8:53:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=531.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hm.. Ideas for upgrades?</span><hr size=1> Imbued Field Plate is easy...  Just need a Cleric of Erollisi Marr to Imbue a few Star Rose Quartz for you.<br>
<br>
Then kill Seafuries for their Mugs of Sea Foam (you can auction for them as well.  In between kills, fish up some Saltwater Seaweed. (only found in OOT, No Drop)  Make sure the person doing the fishing has a decent Brewing skill or is willing to skill-up in brewing.<br>
<br>
Go to this page: <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/secrets/recipes_temper.htm">Tempers</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> for more info on what you'll need for Field Plate &amp; Full Plate Tempers.<br>
<br>
Go to this page: <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/secrets/recipes_smithing_human.htm">Human Smithing</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> for more info on what you'll need for the actual work.<br>
<br>
The hard parts are:<br>
1) Getting a 49+ Enchanter to enchant the HQ ore for Full Plate.<br>
2) Getting Brewing to 135+ to make Tempers.<br>
3) Getting Griffenne Blood for Royal Tempers.<br>
4) Getting a Human Smith to skill 220+ to have a good success rate on combines. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If your Smith friend doesn't have a Geerlok Automatic Hammer (Tinkered item, gives +5% to Smithing), then get them one.  They run about 1kpp and are worth every penny.<br>
<br>
Imbued Field Plate (for Erollisi Marr) has lower AC, but gives +4 Wis &amp; +2 Cha on each piece.  The Cloak, BP, Vambraces &amp; Greaves also have +2 Str.<br>
<br>
Enchanted Silver Full Plate has better AC and gives +3 to +5 Sta &amp; +3 or +4 Agl on each piece. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showPrevMessage?topicID=531.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showNextMessage?topicID=531.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=531.topic&index=6><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.emailToFriend?topicID=531.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.threadControl?topicID=531.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=531.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=531.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="paladinsofnorrathgeneral">General<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm14">Norrath Classic and Kunark<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm15">Velious and Luclin<option value="p